le="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">Concerns are not just about</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal"> Universal Credit. The welfare changes which are now in place threaten the provision of housing in the private rented sector to the less well off.  These will be carried throug</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">h into Universal Credit.  This I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">nquiry provides the opportunity to take a longer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal"> term view. Paying down the deficit is important but as the economy improves longer term decisions are needed about ways in which the private rented sector will play its increasingly important role in housing the less we</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">ll off.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">Our concerns</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal"> around Univers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">al Credit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal"> fall under </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">five</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal">key themes:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; m